content: Welcome to the Online Renju Class weekly lesson!
We give our warmest welcome to new members of renjuclass!
We are happy for such addition to our community!
Now, please press the I AM HERE button, to show that you are here.
bawangwan, coco_yuang, scm2000, Sakuma, cnnrw, Ikon, hate365, mumax, vuquan, Gawa, no_good, shuker, heroabro, namic_99, Alan, ASV777, luwenzhe, true_love, bobo_, rainbowbill, bomb, yusuke_o.
Thank you all! We are ready to begin now! Today we will study renju opening, called i4. In chinese it is called "water moon".
It used to be one of my favorite ones in the past.
However, it is too strong for black, therefore I do not play it in important tournaments.
According to my book records, black win is practically proven everywhere.
We will quickly begin now with checking several 4th moves.
Here, the 5th move to i7 will lead to i7 opening,
Maybe this 5th move is worth to take a quick look.
Black will now develop to the left side space
and for a moment it seems white can become active
but nice contro at g9 will give victory for blacks.
both white pairs are under control.
White is trying hard to defend now, but useless.
Does anyone of you want to show the black VCT here?
any newcomer wants to try win?
the black idea goes this way
Black loses tempo, but keeps controls.
white has many lines, but all useless.

bawangwan, Sakuma, bobo_, ASV777, coco_yuang, mumax, Alan, Gawa, civsnail, cnnrw, vuquan, namic_99, shadewawa, hate365, serdyuk, shuker, rainbowbill, bomb, no_good, luwenzhe, Ikon, true_love, heroabro, yusuke_o, scm2000.

lets not speak when one is trying. if some of you is eager to show, can say ME when we ask people.
and finally black is out of troubles.
why k4 was necessary, you all understand?
We continue with more difficult 4th move now.
this variant was also studied under i3 opening.
note that black cannot win directly here
therefore, a softer move is needed.
black has two VCFs, do you see?
Just beware the trap of water mirror.
Then it is easy to fall into trap
But now, the right side space is too narrow
if you mistakenly made such upper 5th move, then you better change the 9th move
giving you more potential for attack on left side,.
The second 5th move, there are two choices
in my records, in prefer the g8.
but it is very hard to defend
and will help black to win in most cases.
